Displays ANSI colors on the terminal.

USAGE
  tcolor OPTIONS
  tcolor --help

  If no options are provided, all 8-bit colors are shown as if --extended were
  specified.

OPTIONS
Display
  --standard, -s      : display original 4-bit colors in range 0-15
  --extended, -e      : display extended 8-bit colors in range 0-255
  --color, -c COLOR   : display color in range 0-255
  --rgb, -r R G B     : display color using RGB, where each of R/G/B in
                        range 0-255
  --blend, -b FG BG   : display blended foreground and background colors
                        where FG and BG are 8-bit colors in range 0-255

Help
  --help, -h          : print this help
  --version, -v       : print version information
